cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as headline generation and summarization. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on spoken content and ASR (Automatic Speech Recognition) error modeling. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a deep learning approach for headline generation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper uses an Attentive Recurrent Neural Network (ARNN) architecture. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with summarization of spoken content, which can be considered as a form of information network analysis.
